 :tx/rationale "Create task: CRB-6: Reconciliation middleware — extract spec_relevance_scan into a reusable pre-transaction hook that runs on ALL knowledge-producing commands (observe, spec create, task create, write assert). Currently CRB is wired into observe.rs individually. The middleware pattern: every command that produces datoms passes the rationale/title/body text through reconciliation_check(text, store) -> ReconciliationResult { matches: Vec<SpecRelevance>, gate: bool }. Commands call this before transacting. The gate threshold (3+ matches) and bypass flag (--reconciled) are centralized — not duplicated per command. BACKGROUND: The user insight: CRB is semantic graph traversal. Every knowledge-producing command should traverse the semantic neighborhood before creating. This is the same operation as topology coupling (Jaccard on file sets) but on concept space (cosine on keyword sets). Centralizing it as middleware prevents the N*M problem of wiring it into each command individually. TRACES TO: INV-GUIDANCE-025, INV-GUIDANCE-024. ACCEPTANCE: (A) All knowledge-producing commands show related spec. (B) Spec create + task create gate on 3+ matches. (C) Observe shows but doesn't gate. (D) Write assert shows but doesn't gate. (E) Single implementation point — adding a new command gets reconciliation for free. FILE: crates/braid/src/commands/mod.rs (new reconciliation module)"
